## UTM Parameters Explained {#parameters}

| Parameter | Purpose | Required | Example |
|---|---|---|---|
| utm_source | Where the traffic originates | Yes | google, facebook, newsletter, partner_site |
| utm_medium | The marketing channel or mechanism | Yes | cpc, email, social, referral, display |
| utm_campaign | The specific campaign or promotion | Yes | spring_sale, product_launch_q2, brand_awareness |
| utm_content | Differentiates ad variations or link placements | No | hero_cta, sidebar_link, variant_a |
| utm_term | Identifies paid search keywords | No | running_shoes, crm_software |

### How GA4 uses UTMs

GA4 automatically reads UTM parameters and maps them to its traffic source dimensions. This is how Default Channel Groups (Organic Search, Paid Social, Email, etc.) get populated. Incorrect UTMs will cause traffic to be miscategorized.

