## Source and Medium Taxonomy {#taxonomy}

Standardize these values across your entire organization. Every team member and tool should use the same values.

### Recommended source values

| Source Value | When to Use |
|---|---|
| google | Google Ads, Google organic (auto-tagged) |
| facebook | Meta Ads (Facebook + Instagram) |
| instagram | Organic Instagram posts (not ads) |
| linkedin | LinkedIn Ads or organic posts |
| twitter | X/Twitter organic or ads |
| youtube | YouTube ads or descriptions |
| newsletter | Your own email newsletter |
| partner_[name] | Specific partner referrals |
| direct_mail | Physical mail campaigns |
| podcast_[name] | Specific podcast appearances or sponsorships |

### Recommended medium values

| Medium Value | When to Use | GA4 Default Channel |
|---|---|---|
| cpc | Paid search (Google, Bing) | Paid Search |
| paid_social | Paid social ads | Paid Social |
| social | Organic social posts | Organic Social |
| email | Email campaigns and newsletters | Email |
| referral | Partner or affiliate links | Referral |
| display | Banner and display ads | Display |
| video | Video ads (pre-roll, YouTube) | Video |
| affiliate | Affiliate program links | Affiliates |
| retargeting | Retargeting/remarketing campaigns | Display (or custom) |
| sms | Text message campaigns | SMS |
| qr | QR code scans | (custom channel) |

**Important**: GA4 uses the medium value to assign traffic to Default Channel Groups. Using non-standard values (e.g., `paid` instead of `cpc`) will push traffic into "Unassigned." Stick to the values above.

