## UTM Documentation and Governance {#governance}

### Create a UTM tracker

Every team that creates UTMs should log them in a shared document. Minimum fields:

| Field | Purpose |
|---|---|
| Campaign name | What initiative this supports |
| Source | utm_source value |
| Medium | utm_medium value |
| Content | utm_content value (if used) |
| Full URL | The complete tagged URL |
| Owner | Who created it |
| Launch date | When the link goes live |
| Status | Active, completed, or retired |

### Tools for UTM management

- **Google's Campaign URL Builder**: Free, manual entry
- **UTM.io**: Team-based UTM management with templates and validation
- **Spreadsheet formula**: Build your own with string concatenation
- **URL shortener integration**: Use Bitly, Rebrandly, or Dub to shorten tagged URLs

### Governance tips

- Assign one person to own the UTM naming conventions document
- Review UTM consistency monthly in GA4 (check for duplicates, misspellings)
- Build template URLs for recurring campaigns (weekly newsletter, monthly social)
- Use a URL shortener to make tagged links presentable in public-facing contexts

