## Common Mistakes to Avoid {#mistakes}

| Mistake | Problem | Fix |
|---|---|---|
| Inconsistent capitalization | `Google` and `google` create two separate source entries | Enforce lowercase in all UTMs |
| Using spaces | URLs break, parameters get truncated | Use underscores: `spring_sale` |
| Tagging internal links | Overwrites original source attribution | Never put UTMs on links within your own site |
| Too vague | `utm_campaign=promo` is useless in 3 months | Include date and specifics: `spring_promo_2025q1` |
| Forgetting utm_medium | Traffic falls into "Unassigned" channel group | Always include source AND medium |
| Non-standard mediums | `paid` instead of `cpc` breaks channel grouping | Use GA4-compatible medium values |
| No documentation | Nobody remembers what `utm_campaign=abc123` meant | Log every UTM in a shared tracker |
| Double-tagging Google Ads | Manual UTMs conflict with auto-tagging (GCLID) | Let auto-tagging handle Google Ads; use UTMs as fallback only |
